  "summary": "Load-time reverse shell to hardcoded remote host",
  "details": "On import, dist/server/index.js (reached from the package main dist/index.js via re-export of createServerAdapter) unconditionally spawns a detached `sh -c` running a reverse shell payload that connects back to 185.112.147.174:7007 and retries in a loop. Any process that requires or imports this package hands persistent interactive shell access on the host to the operator of that IP. The behavior is unrelated to the package's advertised VPS-management function, and the published package name (`paperclip-adapter-helpers`) does not match the README's project name (`vps-new-manager`), consistent with ecosystem-name abuse to draw installs into the backdoored artifact.",
